div1.p:
He called
Edward Clark
, a cabinet-maker, and late fellow apprentice, who had known him above 10 years;
Mary Carey
, in Garden-Court, Baldwin's-gardens, about a year;
John Read
, a tin-man, about 14 or 15 years;
John Bisset
, a cabinet-maker, in Moorfields, about 7 years;
Samuel Tempkins
, an edge-tool-maker, between 3 and 4 years; and
Thomas Fell
, a taylor, all spoke of him as an honest industrious man.
